	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok far as i know, and correct me anyone if i am wrong. In Mythology and reality, druids were seen as protectors of nature and as well, preist of nature. As a result of this they were not allowed many weapon choices that other people were allowed. Its been like this even in Dungeons and Dragons and every other game i have seen. Druids as a class are often restricted to scythe like weapons (having to do with harvest etc..) and blunt weapons. For some reason Scimitars were excepted and a sword called a Kopesh were also used, but not in everquest. So Preist of nature thing would acount bow's are used for hunting IE hurting natural things, becasue all you do with a bow is kill something so therefore druids would not use. Rangers however being more of the Hunter/traker ideal would.<br>&nbsp;<br>Regnon Plainswalker Lvl 55 Druid of NIHIL Bertox<br>What the heck was that?.....darn bixie stinger</td></tr>
