	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jul 8th 4:45 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I understand your confusion.&nbsp;&nbsp;I had the same problem when I first started playing.  And you’re right, ultimately you’ll have to make your own decisions and live with the consequences.  All I can do is tell you my own experiences.  When you do something that will effect your faction for either good or ill, be that killing something or doing a quest, you will get a message telling you what faction has been effected and whether that faction has gotten better for worse.  If my druid walks out into East Commons and kills a bear I will NOT get a faction message.  I’ve killed hundreds and I’ve NEVER gotten such a message.  And the bears are amiable to me still.  Try killing one of the orcs and see what happens.  You’ll get several faction hits.  The orcs will like you less and some NPCs will like you better.  The same happens when you hand in a the orc belts.  Its often difficult to figure what NPCs are on what faction, but one thing is constant; if you get a faction hit you’ll get a message telling you so.  <br><br>The only exception to faction hits for normal animals that I’ve ever come across is in Surefall Glade.  That is a sacred place.  Killing the bears there is taken as a personal affront by Tunare as you are, basically, in her temple.  But outside of Surefall, there is no penalty for killing bears and other such animals.<br><br>If you want to role-play your druid and set personal limits, that’s up to you.  For myself, I refuse to hunt intelligent, good aligned creatures.  Such creatures, at least for me, include centaurs and pixies.  Brownies, however, are evil little bastards that deserve to be killed and turned into chocolate.  *grins*  But druids have to keep a balance in nature and death is a part of that balance.  So I don’t have any problem killing bears and lions, as long as there is no danger of extinction.  <br><br>&nbsp;<br><b>Namir Shadowstalker</b><br>Wood Elf Ranger, 51st Season<br><b>Calabar Silverthorn</b><br>Wood Elf Druid, 51st Season<br><b>Pait Spiritwalker</b><br>Vah Shir Shaman, 50th Season<br><br><b>Seventh Hammer</b></td></tr>
