	   <tr><td colspan=2>Not being able to hunt animals is strictly a myth.&nbsp;&nbsp;People who roleplay often make themselves rules about killing animals, but it is a personal decision.<br><br>The only animals you should Not kill in the game are the Surefall Glade sacred animals (those animals in the surefall glade zone).  Anywhere else is fair game, whether or not the animal is amiable to you or not.  I have a lvl 40 druid, and when I needed skins for tailoring, I took on every animal I could find, without ill effects.<br><br>If you Want to give your character roleplaying restrictions, you can.  (For myself, my druid always loots every part of the animal, whether it is needed or not, and leaves nothing lying on the ground, out of respect.)  But this is strictly up to you.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
