	   <a name=102554802041123></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102554802041123><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=8&mid=102554802041123>RE: Questions about Quadding at lvl 34</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=8&mid=102554802041123#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=166643><span id=Scholar>tamarask</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>51 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Jul 1st 2:37 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.13]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>As you probably realize, it's a good idea to get your wisdom as high as possible to raise your mana pool. Until then, make friends with enchanters who can cast a form of clarity on you prior to your quading. <br><br>That being said, you will get more experience quading in an outdoor zone than grouping in an outdoor zone. Mainly because you can kill 4 mobs at a time and not share the experience with a group. <br><br>Snare is a shorter length than Ensnare, so when you get that upgraded snare spell, always use it. If you can't snare the mobs and keep them snared during the length of the quad, then you will not be able to quad kite efficiently.&nbsp;&nbsp;If a mob breaks snare during the quad, then you will waste precious time and mana resnaring. <br><br>You will probably get more experience in a full dungeon group than quadding. The reasons for this opinion are: 1) you get a dungeon bonus and a full group experience bonus. 2)Less down time in a good group who can chain pull multiple mobs efficiently.<br><br>In outdoor zones, as long as you have the mana to sustain your snares and AE dd's, quadding is very very good experience and, for me at least, much better experience than in a full outdoor group.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
