	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Jun 23rd 1:09 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.13]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Horses are merely an illusion buff that give increased speed. There are a few different kinds and they all have different horse colors and speeds. The fastest horses are the most expensive. You purchase a bridle which goes in your range slot. Then, right click it to get your speed enhancement and the horse illusion.&nbsp;&nbsp;I believe high level Paladins get Holy Steed. Not sure though if this is a spell they buy or an ability. I can't seem to find any reference to it in the spell guides.<br><br>For sowing classes, like ours, it's just a status symbol. Pretty useless as we have several speed enhancing spells already. (Sow, Spirit of Cheetah, Scale of Wolf, wolf form)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
