	   <tr><td colspan=2>I just wanted to respond to a small portion of the post. The one about being too afraid or annoyed to hide behind an anon flag in newbie zones. I'm a level 55 druid. I always go anon in newbie zones. Not because I'm &quot;afraid&quot; (not sure what you mean by that) but because when I'm on, I'm doing something, tradeskilling or fighting. And as I'm guilded, I'm also chatting with my friends. Nothing is more annoying than having scrolled text from strangers saying &quot;sow me! heal me! port me! buff me! Can you help me with a quest, it's REALLY important&quot; all from level 1-10 peeps. And then having to scroll back to find out what the people I want to talk to are saying.<br>When you are a high level druid, you will know what I mean. And yeah, nothing is more annoying than peeps begging me for money or weapons constantly. At level 29, you can port to maybe 4 zones. At level 55 I can port to all the zones and trust me, everyone knows it and wants me to stop what I'm doing NOW and help them with a CR. About the only stranger tells I'll reply to when I'm busy are other druids having questions about their epics or spells.<br><br>Tams Thunderfang<br>55 druid.<br>Quellious<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
