	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings,<br><br>As far as I know, this isn't true, not for killing non-named wolves and other animals. I spent a long time in my teen levels hunting E and W Commons for pelts for my tailoring. I killed innumerable wolves, lions, pumas, plains cats, bears and kodiaks. There is no faction hit for killing these. The rangers on the hill in EC and the druids at the WC ring never attacked me. I've had no problem trading/training since then either.<br><br>For those that wonder about a Druid killing animals - Nature is cruel, and the sentient races are top of the food chain. Survival of the fittest, and all that! Besides, with the numbers that appear throughout Norrath, aren't they almost pests and vermin?!<br><br><br>Fight on!<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Kelanthor<br>Wood Elf Druid of the 41st Circle<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=212672" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=212672</a></td></tr>
