	   <tr><td colspan=2>That level was when I gave up soloing in favor of massive xp. Get yourself over to Highkeep, and get into a room group (either guard or warrior or the spinoffs). I went from 2 yellows into 27 to 29th level in 5 hours! If you're like me, you prefer to solo, but for getting to those next spell levels, it's definitely worth it, and the loot is nice, too. As a smith, the HQ ore definitely came in handy.<br><br>But, if you're determined to solo, try the wooly mammoths in Everfrost. Fear-kite them near the mammoth plateau, and get the tusks (sell for 6-10pp) for loot. You can kite red mammoths, although at your level there will only be one that's red (the corrupted -- leave it alone for now). Enjoy!<br>&nbsp;<br>-- <br>[Druid] Lambeau Farstrider (Human)<br>[Rogue] Gripp Tinkersnout (Gnome)<br>&lt;Tragic Heroes&gt; -- Saryrn</td></tr>
